This was my first time visiting this location. I ordered a spicy sandwich and after tasting it, it wasn’t as spicy as the other ones I’ve had before. I returned to the cashier and asked if she had given me a mild by accident. She stepped to the back where she asked the food handler if this was spicy. The food handler yelled, it’s spicy what more she wants some hot sauce? They then started to speak in another language and I’m sure it was anything pleasant because I heard something along the line of, “this is just Popeyes”. I guess I shouldn’t  have any expectations of decent service or what I ordered. The manager standing next to her said that’s how spicy it comes. She had a very nasty attitude so I asked for a refund because at that point I no longer wanted to have any additional interaction with that type of attitude. She said I could wait 7 minutes for another sandwich or until she’s done with her customer order for the refund. If that’s the behavior and attitude of a manager, no wonder the staff is so rude and not helpful to customers over something so simple.

I did a mobile order for this exact location and it was a terrible experience. If I am ordering on my phone, it's clearly because I don't have time to wait on a line to order my food, then wait for it to be packed up. I ordered ahead of time, went into the place and saw that my food still was NOT ready. I went up to the cashier and she goes "what mobile order?"... she then looks through a huge pile of receipts on the counter just to finally find the one that correlates to what I had ordered. Mind you, all I ordered was a regular fry and 3 piece tenders, nothing extravagant, but it still took like an extra 6 minutes just for me to receive my food as if it was being made fresh, which it was not, I saw them taking the food from under heat lamps. The staff is unprofessional in my eyes and I don't feel as though customers should be treated this way. I've worked in fast food for a while and I understand what it's like to be on both sides of the counter, but customer service needs to be better because some of the workers also have attitude problems.
